main event: A resident of Duluth, Minnesota reported observing a UFO on December 6, 1967 at approximately 10:15 pm.
interesting points: The object appeared larger than a normal star or planet, and fluctuated in intensity, sometimes appearing very bright and then fading.
The object remained in view for approximately 15 minutes before suddenly accelerating and disappearing from sight in a matter of seconds.
The witness called his wife to observe the object, but she was unable to see it from their house.
The witness stated that the object behaved in a manner that he had never seen before with any conventional aircraft.
The movements of the object were described as completely unexplainable in terms of known aerodynamics or propulsion systems.
sighted object: a bright, yellowish-white light that appeared larger than a normal star or planet
